article.headline: CS Northridge 89, UC Riverside 69
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Calvin Chitwood scored 16 points, grabbed 13 rebounds and blocked three shots to lead Cal State Northridge to a 89-69 victory Thursday night against UC Riverside. The win ended the Matadors' four-game losing streak. Jayme Miller added a career-best 16 points for Northridge (11-12, 4-6 Big West), and helped spark a 17-3 run that put the team ahead 33-17 with just over five minutes to play in the half. Larry Cunningham led Riverside with 24 points, while Chris Johnson added 19. Riverside made 13 of its 22 field goals from behind the 3-point line, but shot just 37 percent from the field.
